intext: Pileus 9-15 cm in diameter, at first globose, then hemispherical or hemispherical with distinctly truncate margin, much later truncate-conic and finally plano-convex, dingy whitish or uniformly ochraceous to brown (occasionally uniformly grey where exposed to wind and sunshine), except for the truncate marginal zone which white or greyish, frequently with small, triangular scales sparsely, concentrically arranged in the middle, fibrillose in the peri-marginal zone which may become rimose, smooth (white or grey) or with triangular concentrically arranged squamules on a white background in the distinctly separated marginal zone.
